    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b4af57cc_f522562b",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/internal/sshtest/default.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-19T04:59:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why don\u0027t we call NewTestData multiple times to start multiple servers, rather than letting one TestData own multiple servers?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "06d30c52ae3ff8637f43f7ebb91f66440bb7eaa8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e16f46c6_cd930d40",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/internal/sshtest/default.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 1431492
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-19T17:09:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It was because of the key file. Tast config use a single key file. Unless there is a need to support multiple key files in Tast, I think it would be better to use one single test data.",
      "parentUuid": "b4af57cc_f522562b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 57,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "06d30c52ae3ff8637f43f7ebb91f66440bb7eaa8",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ed341b00_959e4d2d",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/internal/sshtest/default.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 57,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-22T03:16:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "OK, then I\u0027m fine with letting TestData own multiple servers. But I still want to resolve assymmetricity between the \"primary\" server and additional servers.\n\nWhat do you think about updating TestData to:\n\n type TestData struct {\n   Srvs        []*SSHServer\n   UserKeyFile string\n }\n \nand NewTestData to:\n\n func NewTestData(handlers ...ExecHandler) *TestData\n\nso that users can start multiple servers by passing several handlers to NewTestData?",
      "parentUuid": "e16f46c6_cd930d40",
